'''Miss World 1984''', the 34th edition of the [[Miss World]] pageant, was held on 15 November 1984 at the [[Royal Albert Hall]] in London, UK.<ref name="huffingtonpost.co.uk"/> The winner was [[Astrid Carolina Herrera]] from Venezuela. She was crowned by Miss World 1983, [[Sarah-Jane Hutt]] of the United Kingdom. The 1st and 2nd runners-up were Constance Ellen (Connie) Fitzpatrick from Canada, and Lou-Anne Caroline Ronchi from Australia. The event was viewed by 17.1 million people in the UK.<ref name="Thussu 2008 p. 37">{{cite book | last=Thussu | first=D.K. | title=News as Entertainment: The Rise of Global Infotainment | publisher=SAGE Publications | year=2008 | isbn=978-1-4462-3331-3 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L-5jny8sijsC&pg=PA37 | accessdate=January 26, 2016 | page=37}}</ref>
