'''Mollie Olgin''', 19, was murdered on June 22, 2012 in [[Violet Andrews Park]] in [[Portland, Texas]]. David Malcolm Strickland, 25, [[sexual assault|sexually assaulted]] her and her girlfriend '''Mary Kristene "Kris" Chapa''', 18, before shooting them both [[execution-style murder|execution-style]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Alyssa|last=Newcomb|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/texas-lesbian-couple-survivor-remembers-night-shooting/story?id=16689655|title=Texas Lesbian Couple: Survivor Remembers Night of Shooting|date=July 2, 2012|work=ABC News|access-date=July 16, 2017}}</ref> Olgin was pronounced dead at the scene and Chapa was taken to hospital in critical condition due to a bullet wound in her head.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dahl|first1=Julia|title=Same-Sex Teen Couple Shot: Texas Rangers investigating shooting of Mollie Olgin and Mary Chapa|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/same-sex-teen-couple-shot-texas-rangers-investigating-shooting-of-mollie-olgin-and-mary-chapa/|accessdate=July 17, 2017|work=CBS News|date=June 28, 2012|language=en}}</ref> Following intensive care and concerns that the bullet may have left her completely paralyzed,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Leitsinger|first1=Miranda|title=Brother of lesbian teen shot in head: She's 'fighting'|url=http://usnews.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/06/28/12459116-brother-of-lesbian-teen-shot-in-head-shes-fighting?lite|accessdate=July 17, 2017|work=MSNBC|date=June 18, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120701062452/http://usnews.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/06/28/12459116-brother-of-lesbian-teen-shot-in-head-shes-fighting?lite|archivedate=July 1, 2012}}</ref> Chapa regained mobility in the left side of her body.<ref name="GLAAD verdict reached" />
On September 28, 2016 a jury found Strickland guilty of [[capital murder]] and [[aggravated sexual assault]]. Since the prosecution did not seek the [[death penalty]] for Strickland, he was sentenced to [[life imprisonment]].<ref name="GLAAD verdict reached">{{Cite web|url=https://www.glaad.org/blog/verdict-reached-4-years-after-deadly-attack-tx-lesbian-teen-couple|title=Verdict reached 4 years after deadly attack on TX lesbian teen couple|date=September 28, 2016|work=GLAAD|first=Alexandra|last=Bolles|access-date=July 16, 2017}}</ref>
