{{Infobox Film Festival | name = Warsaw Jewish Film Festival | image = | caption = | location = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]] | awards = | founded = 2003 | host = | number = | language = [[Polish language|Polish]], English, other | website = [http://www.wjff.pl/en/ Warsaw Jewish Film Festival] }} [[File:Www.wjff.pl-en.jpg|alt=www.wjff.pl|thumb|Warsaw Jewish Film Festival WJFF.pl]] The '''Warsaw Jewish Film Festival''' ('''WJFF.pl''') is an annual Jewish [[film festival]] held in [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]], since 2003.
WARSAW JEWISH FILM FESTIVAL (WJFF.PL) IS THE FIRST EVER AND THE LARGEST JEWISH FILM FESTIVAL IN POLAND AND EASTERN EUROPE. Established in 2003 has 15 years of experience acquiring some of the finest international, thematically Jewish, films. Movies which are dedicated to exploring Jewish culture, history and contemporary life of Jewish communities from around the globe.
The Festival is a member of the Association of European Jewish Film Festivals.
The 16th edition will take place on November 12-18, 2018 at the POLIN Museum of the history of Polish Jews. [[File:Www.wjff.pl-en.jpg|thumb]]
